shame:
Looks for a player on Warships Today. You can also look up players by pinging them if they are in the shamelist. Support all regions, default is NA. The region codes are: 'NA', 'EU', 'RU', 'AS' 
Example usage: `?shame MaT1g3R`, `?shame flamu EU`
volume:
Sets the volume of the currently playing song.
Example usage: `?volume 50`
addshame:
Add yourself to the shamelist. If you are already in the shamelist, it will be overwritten by the new player name. Support all regions, default is NA. The region codes are: 'NA', 'EU', 'RU', 'AS'
Example usage: `?addshame MY_WOWS_USER_NAME`, `?addshame flamu EU`
currency:
Converts currency.
Example usage: '?currency JPY CAD 18000' this converts 18000 JPY to CAD
roll:
Rolls some dice.
Example usage: `?roll 3d6` This rolls 6 sided die, 3 times.
stackoverflow:
Searches for an answer on stackoverflow, this feature is highly experimental.
Example usage: `?stackoverflow Python linked list`
avatar:
Displays the avatar of mentioned user. MUST mention user.
Example usage: `?avatar name`
shamelist: Prints out the entire shamelist for this server.
salt:
Probability of something happening over some amount of tries.
Example usage: `?salt 0.01 100` this is the same as `?salt 1% 100`
skip: Vote to skip a song. The song requester can automatically skip. 3 skip votes are needed for the song to be skipped.
anime:
Searches for an anime on MAL.
Example usage `?anime Madoka Magica`
playing: Shows info about the currently played song.
ship:
Looks for a ship on the WG wiki.
Example usage: `?ship shimakaze`
repeat:
Repeats text for x amout of times, max is 5 times.
Example usage: `?repeat 5 Dank memes`
play:
Plays a song.
If there is a song currently in the queue, then it isqueued until the next song is done playing.
This command automatically searches as well from YouTube.The list of supported sites can be found here:<https://rg3.github.io/youtube-dl/supportedsites.html>
Example usage: `?play Poland is not yet lost`
joined:
Show when a member joined the server, MUST mention the user.
Example usage: `?joined name`
choose:
Choose an item between multiple items, separated by space.
Example usage: `?choose item1 item2 item_3`
stop: Stops playing audio and leaves the voice channel. This also clears the queue.
pmall:
Sends a custom pm to all mentioned member, this is an admin only command.
Example usage: `?pmall @user1 @user2 @user3 write your content after the mentions`
summon: Summons the bot to join your voice channel.
latex:
Render a latex equation.
Example usage: `?latex \int_0^1 \frac{log(x)}{x^2 + 1}`
info: Displays some info about the bot.
lewd: Displays a random lewd reaction face.
osu:
Return information for an osu! user. No filter for searching in standard mode, add one of: `--osu, --Taiko, --CTB, --mania` to the end of your search to specify the mode.
Example usage: `?osu potateau`, `?osu Bukkake Blast --CTB`
newsheet: Creates a new spreadsheet, this will delete the old one.
addmatch:
Adds a new match to the current spreadsheet, note this will override any match on the same day.
Example usage: `?addmatch mon March 6th, 10:00PM EST`, `?addmatch Monday mar.6 10:00AM PST`
removematch: Removes a match from the current spreadsheet, note this will remove any data that's associated with that match.
joinmatch:
Joins a match or multiple matches on the curent spreadsheet.
Example usage: `?joinmatch mon`, `?joinmatch mon tue wed Thursday`
quitmatch:
Quit match/matches on the current spreadsheet. 
Example usage: `?quitmatch mon`, `?quitmatch mon tue wed Thursday`
